Refactored the release pipeline to load steps from a registry of built-in step functions, paving the way for configurable release pipelines defined in `repository.toml`. Step functions now share a uniform contract `(step_id, title, settings, state, **kwargs) -> bool`. Added the `local_step` built-in, which imports a project-local callable (via `entrypoint = "module.path:callable"`) and runs it under the standard step contract. @ericof
